[[File:PE-mapa-Poção.png|thumb|right|250px|Location of Poção within Pernambuco.]]
[[File:Bandeirapocao.JPG|thumb|right|160px|Poção Flag]] '''Poção''' is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located at 241&nbsp;km away from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco. Has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 11.503 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[Paraiba]] state ('''N'''); [[Pesqueira, Pernambuco|Pesqueira]] ('''S''' and '''W'''); [[Jataúba]] ('''E'''). * Area - 199.74&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 1000 m * Hidrography - [[Capibaribe River|Capibaribe]] and [[Ipojuca River|Ipojuca rivers]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[Hipoxerófila]] * Clima - [[Semi arid]] * Annual average temperature - 19.5 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 241&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Poção''' are based in [[agribusiness]], especially [[beans]], [[maize|corn]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[sheep]], [[goats]] and [[poultry]].
